#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn16.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn16.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 16 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 16 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Kassapavagga "
msgstr "1. Kassapa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Santuṭṭhasutta → santuṭṭhisuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn16.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Santuṭṭhasutta "
msgstr "1. Content "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.194, sc1
msgctxt "sn16.1:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Santuṭṭhāyaṃ → santuṭṭhoyaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn16.1:1.2"
msgid "“Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, Kassapa is content with any kind of robe, and praises such contentment. "

#. VAR: agadhito → agathito (si)
msgctxt "sn16.1:1.3"
msgid "na ca cīvarahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca cīvaraṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca cīvaraṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "He doesn’t try to get hold of a robe in an improper way. He doesn’t get upset if he doesn’t get a robe. And if he does get a robe, he uses it untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn16.1:2.1"
msgid "Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena piṇḍapātena, itarītarapiṇḍapātasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca piṇḍapātahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca piṇḍapātaṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca piṇḍapātaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "Kassapa is content with any kind of alms-food … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn16.1:3.1"
msgid "Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena senāsanena, itarītarasenāsanasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca senāsanahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca senāsanaṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca senāsanaṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "Kassapa is content with any kind of lodging … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn16.1:4.1"
msgid "Santuṭṭhāyaṃ, bhikkhave, kassapo itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, itarītaragilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādī; na ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjati; aladdhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ na paritassati; laddhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ agadhito amucchito anajjhāpanno ādīnavadassāvī nissaraṇapañño paribhuñjati. "
msgstr "Kassapa is content with any kind of medicines and supplies for the sick … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.195, sc5
msgctxt "sn16.1:5.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ: ‘santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena cīvarena, itarītaracīvarasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādino; na ca cīvarahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissāma; "
msgstr "So you should train like this: ‘We will be content with any kind of robe, and praise such contentment. We won’t try to get hold of a robe in an improper way. "

msgctxt "sn16.1:5.2"
msgid "aladdhā ca cīvaraṃ na ca paritassissāma; laddhā ca cīvaraṃ agadhitā amucchitā anajjhāpannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjissāma’. "
msgstr "We won’t get upset if we don’t get a robe. And if we do get a robe, we’ll use it untied, uninfatuated, unattached, seeing the drawback, and understanding the escape.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.1:5.3"
msgid "(Evaṃ sabbaṃ kātabbaṃ.) "
msgstr "(All should be treated the same way.) "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn16.1:6.1"
msgid "‘Santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena piṇḍapātena … pe … "
msgstr "‘We will be content with any kind of alms-food …’ "

msgctxt "sn16.1:6.2"
msgid "santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena senāsanena … pe … "
msgstr "‘We will be content with any kind of lodging …’ "

msgctxt "sn16.1:6.3"
msgid "santuṭṭhā bhavissāma itarītarena gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārena, itarītaragilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārasantuṭṭhiyā ca vaṇṇavādino; na ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu anesanaṃ appatirūpaṃ āpajjissāma aladdhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ na paritassissāma; laddhā ca gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ agadhitā amucchitā anajjhāpannā ādīnavadassāvino nissaraṇapaññā paribhuñjissāmā’ti. "
msgstr "‘We will be content with any kind of medicines and supplies for the sick …’ "

msgctxt "sn16.1:6.4"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "That’s how you should train. "

#. VAR: ovadissāmi yo vā panassa → yo vā pana (si) | yo vā (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn16.1:6.5"
msgid "Kassapena vā hi vo, bhikkhave, ovadissāmi yo vā panassa kassapasadiso, ovaditehi ca pana vo tathattāya paṭipajjitabban”ti. "
msgstr "I will exhort you with the example of Kassapa or someone like him. You should practice accordingly.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn16.1:6.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

